    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify">(1)<b> DEFINITION OF BENEFICIAL OWNERSHIP</b></p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify"><b>Article 1, para. 2, lett. pp) of Italian Legislative Decree no. 231 of 21st November 2007 – “beneficial ownership”</b>: "the individual(s), other than the client, in whose ultimate interests the continuing relationship will be established, the professional service will be rendered or the transaction will be executed."</p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify"><b>Art. 20, Legislative Decree. no. 231 of 21 November 2007 231 as amended – “Criteria for determining the beneficial ownership of customers that are not natural persons”.</b></p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify">1. The beneficial owner of customers other that natural persons is the natural person or persons to whom the direct or indirect ownership of the entity or the relative control can be ultimately attributed.</p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify">2. If the customer is a stock company:</p>
    <ol style="list-style-type: lower-latin;text-align:justify; margin-top:.0001pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; font-size:8.5pt;">
      <li>ownership of a shareholding that exceeds 25 percent of the customer’s capital held by a natural person indicates direct ownership;</li>
      <li>ownership of the percentage of a shareholding that exceeds 25 percent of the customer’s capital owned through subsidiaries, trust companies or a third party indicates indirect ownership.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify">3. If examination of the proprietary structure does not permit univocal identification of the natural person or persons that the direct or indirect ownership of the entity can be attributed to, the beneficial owner is the natural person or persons who ultimately control it through:</p>
    <ol style="list-style-type: lower-latin;text-align:justify; margin-top:.0001pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; font-size:8.5pt;">
      <li>control of the majority of votes exercisable in the ordinary shareholders’ meeting;</li>
      <li>control of votes that are enough to exercise a dominant influence in the ordinary shareholders’ meeting;</li>
      <li>the existence of specific contractual constraints enabling a dominating influence.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify">4. If the customer is a private legal person, pursuant to President of the Republic Decree no. 361 of 10 February 2000, the following are jointly identified as beneficial owners:</p>
    <ol style="list-style-type: lower-latin;text-align:justify; margin-top:.0001pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; font-size:8.5pt;">
      <li>the founders, if alive;</li>
      <li>the beneficiaries when identified or easily identifiable;</li>
      <li>the holders of legal representation, management and administration powers.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify">5. If application of the criteria in the previous points does not enable univocal identification of one or more beneficial owners, the beneficial owner coincides with the natural person or persons owning, in compliance with their respective organisational or statutory structures, the powers of legal representation, management or administration of the company or the customer not a natural person.</p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify">6. Obligated entities will keep records of checks carried out aimed at identifying beneficial owners.</p>

