                    </b>
                </p>
                
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify">(2) <b>DEFINITION OF POLITICALLY EXPOSED PERSONS</b>  </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;"><b>Article 1, para. 2, lett. dd), Italian Legislative Decree no. 231 of 21st November 2007 – "Politically exposed persons": </b></p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">politically exposed persons: an individual who is or has, at any time in the preceding year, been entrusted with a prominent public function, as well as their relatives and known close associates, as listed below: </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1) individuals who are or have been entrusted with prominent public functions are those who hold or have held the office of: </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.1 the President of the Republic, Prime Minister, Minister, Deputy Minister and Secretary, Regional President, Regional Council Executive Committee member, Mayor of a provincial capital or metropolitan city, Mayor of a municipality with a population not less than 15,000 inhabitants, as well as similar roles in foreign countries; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.2 deputy, senator, European parliamentarian, regional councillor, as well as similar roles in foreign countries; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.3 member of a political party's Central Executive Committee;</p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.4 Constitutional Court Judge, Magistrate of the Court of Cassation or the Court of Auditors, councillor of State and other members of the Council of Administrative Justice for the Sicilian Region, as well as similar roles in foreign countries; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.5 member of the governing bodies of central banks and of independent authorities; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.6 ambassador, Chargé d'Affaires or equivalent roles in foreign countries, senior officers in the armed forces or similar roles in foreign countries; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.7 member of the administrative, management or control bodies of businesses controlled, even indirectly, by the Italian State or by a foreign country, or whose shares, either a majority or the totality, are held by Regions, by provincial capitals and metropolitan cities and by municipalities with a total population of not less than 15,000 inhabitants; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.8 general manager of ASL [local area health authority] and hospital companies, university hospital companies and other Italian National Health Service agencies. </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">1.9 director, deputy director and member of the management body or individual carrying out equivalent functions in international organisations; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">2) relatives of politically exposed persons include: parents, spouse or civil partner or cohabitee or similar institution to the politically exposed person, children and their spouses as well as their child's civil partner or cohabitee or similar institution; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">3) individuals with close ties to a politically exposed person are: </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">3.1 individuals who, pursuant to this decree, jointly with the politically exposed person, have effective ownership of legal entities, trusts and similar legal arrangements or who have close business relationships with the politically exposed person; </p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify;">3.2 individuals who formally hold total control of an entity well-known for being constituted, in fact, in the interest and for the benefit of a politically exposed person.</p>
    <p class="MsoFootnoteText" style="text-align:justify; margin-top:20px">(3) ‘Type of business activity’ means the business sector that the natural person is involved in, like Business sector and NACE for legal persons e.g. chemical production, carpentry, construction, sale of foodstuffs, cultivation of agricultural products, rental services and leasing etc.</p>
